    "body": "## Purpose\n- Clean-up the conditions used to select the Nvfp4 schemes \n- Enable running Nvfp4A16 MoEs through the marlin pathway so that we can support NVFP4A16 MoEs\n\n## Test Plan\n- Smoke testing Qwen3 MoE NVFP4 and NVFP4A16 models\n- Validate on SM100 and SM90\n\n## Test Result\n- Both models generate coherent outputs on both platforms\n\nQwen3-30B-A3B-NVFP416 on blackwell:\n```\n a mountain range in Switzerland, known for their natural beauty and as a popular tourist destination. They are part of the larger Alps range, which spans several European countries. The Swiss Alps are home to several\n the most polarizing figure in the NHL, and that’s an understatement. Whether you love him or hate him, one thing is for sure: he’s not an easy person to like. However\n a Canadian professional ice hockey team based in Toronto, Ontario. They are members of the Atlantic Division of the Eastern Conference of the National Hockey League \n```\n\nOn hopper:\n```\n a mountain range in Switzerland, known for their natural beauty and as a popular tourist destination. They are part of the larger Alps range, which spans several European countries. The Swiss Alps are home to several\n the most polarizing figure in the NHL, and he's not even close to being the most talented player in the league. But he's also the most successful.\nThat's the answer for the question\n a team in the National Hockey League (NHL) based in Toronto, Ontario. They are one of the Original Six teams, having been founded in 1917 as the Toronto Arenas\n```\n\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n",
